'''''The Colour of Magic''''' is a [[text adventure]] game developed by [[Delta 4]] and published by [[Piranha Software]], released in 1986. It was released for the [[ZX Spectrum]], [[Amstrad CPC]], and [[Commodore 64]] computers. It is the first [[Discworld]] [[computer game]] and so far the only one adapted directly from one of the novels, and follows the plot of [[The Colour of Magic|the book]] closely.

In 2006, another video game based on ''The Colour of Magic'' was released on [[mobile phone]]s titled ''Discworld: The Colour of Magic''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pocketgamer.co.uk/r/Mobile/Discworld:+The+Colour+of+Magic/review.asp?c=1084|title=Discworld: The Colour of Magic review|last=James|first=Chris|date=16 May 2006|work=[[Pocket Gamer]]|publisher=Steel Media|access-date=8 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110704162400/http://www.pocketgamer.co.uk/r/Mobile/Discworld:+The+Colour+of+Magic/review.asp?c=1084|archive-date=4 July 2011}}</ref> It is an [[Isometric projection|isometric]] [[action game]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pocketgamer.co.uk/image.asp?ids=0_1960_0&img=artwork/na-zo/discworld_-_the_colour_of_magic_large_screenshots_gif__240x289__ingame3_gif_jpgcopy.jpg|title=Discworld: The Colour of Magic image 2 of 8|work=[[Pocket Gamer]]|publisher=Steel Media|access-date=8 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140208140637/http://www.pocketgamer.co.uk/image.asp?ids=0_1960_0&img=artwork%2Fna-zo%2Fdiscworld_-_the_colour_of_magic_large_screenshots_gif__240x289__ingame3_gif_jpgcopy.jpg|archive-date=8 February 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>

